      "content": "I'm glad you're considering other options, but I must stress that antibiotics like ciprofloxacin are not recommended during pregnancy unless prescribed by a healthcare professional. Taking antibiotics without a prescription can lead to unnecessary side effects and potential harm to both you and your baby. Sinus infections can be managed with safer alternatives such as saline nasal rinses, staying hydrated, and resting. If your symptoms persist or worsen, please consult your healthcare provider for a safe and appropriate treatment plan. Your health and your baby's health are the top priorities. Stay safe and take care!",
      "source": "target",
